components.name: Fetch Brokerage Holdings
components.description: Retrieves holdings CSV data from a brokerage account via a simulated API and returns a dictionary containing the brokerage ID and holdings list.

components.name: Analyze Portfolio
components.description: Calculates portfolio metrics such as total value, allocation percentages, and risk score from holdings data.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful fetch of brokerage holdings

components.name: Aggregate and Rebalance
components.description: Aggregates analysis results from all brokerages and computes rebalancing trades to meet target allocations.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after all portfolio analyses complete successfully

components.name: Generate Trade Orders
components.description: Generates a timestamped CSV file containing trade orders based on the calculated rebalancing trades.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after rebalancing trades are generated

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

brokerage_id.description: Brokerage identifier used to fetch holdings

sources: Simulated brokerage API providing holdings CSV data for each of the 5 brokerage accounts (BROKERAGE_001005).
sinks: Local CSV file (trade_orders_YYYYMMDD.csv) containing the generated rebalancing trade orders.
intermediate_datasets: holdings_data_dict  dictionary with brokerage ID and mock holdings list (output of fetch_brokerage_holdings).
portfolio_analysis_results  metrics dictionary per brokerage (output of analyze_portfolio).
aggregated_rebalancing_trades  list of trade instructions computed by aggregate_and_rebalance.
